primary.request: register a new account on the website
primary.context: Customer received a message stating their ownership type requires special handling for registration
primary.detail: The agent verified the caller's identity using contract ID and name, then sent a Clubhouse registration link via email.

steps: Caller requested help with website registration due to a special handling error message.
Agent attempted lookup by phone number (failed) and then by contract ID (success).
Agent performed identity verification; caller provided a secondary owner's name when the first didn't match.
Agent confirmed contact details on file and sent the registration link.
Caller confirmed they would use the link to create the account.

clarifications.note: Agent clarifying if user needs registration or password reset
Agent asking for spelling of name for verification

corrections.note: User clarifies multiple owners on contract after name mismatch

actions.detail: Lookup by Brazilian phone number failed to find record
Verified using secondary owner name and state
Sent Clubhouse registration link to email on file

insights.summary: The customer wanted to register for the online portal but was blocked by a system message; the AI successfully verified the account and sent a registration link.
insights.verbatim: Perfect. So I have to log in in Vacatia, the new website.
